Phase 3 is complete and working well. I'd like to continue building the application without changing the existing Pivot Configuration contract or backend APIs.

Please use the current Pivot Configuration JSON and the existing /api/pivot endpoint exactly as implemented.

The goal of this phase is to render the computed pivot results in a clean, Excel-like experience using AG Grid Community (plain JavaScript).

I'm not looking for an exact clone of Microsoft Excel, but I do want users to feel familiar with the workflow.

Please improve the Pivot page with the following functionality.

--------------------------------------------------
1. Generate Pivot
--------------------------------------------------

When the user clicks "Generate Pivot":

- Validate the configuration
- Call the existing compute endpoint
- Display a loading overlay while the request is running
- Disable the Generate button until the request completes
- Display friendly error messages if the request fails

Do not change the request payload.

--------------------------------------------------
2. Render the Pivot Result
--------------------------------------------------

Use AG Grid to display the returned pivot data.

The grid should support:

- column resizing
- column reordering
- sorting
- filtering
- text search
- row striping
- sticky header
- pagination
- horizontal scrolling
- responsive layout

Columns should be generated dynamically from the response.

--------------------------------------------------
3. Row Selection
--------------------------------------------------

Enable checkbox selection.

Support:

- single row selection
- multiple row selection
- Select All
- Clear Selection

Display a small summary above the grid showing:

Selected Rows:
Selected Groups:
Total Rows Returned:

The selected rows will be used in the email module later, so keep the selected row objects available in JavaScript.

--------------------------------------------------
4. Compact and Tabular Layout
--------------------------------------------------

The backend already returns the layout information.

Render both layouts correctly.

Tabular layout should display each row field separately.

Compact layout should display the combined row hierarchy cleanly.

--------------------------------------------------
5. Grand Totals
--------------------------------------------------

If Grand Totals are enabled:

Display them clearly at the bottom of the grid.

Style them differently from normal rows.

--------------------------------------------------
6. Row Totals
--------------------------------------------------

If Row Totals are enabled:

Display the total column with a different style.

--------------------------------------------------
7. Column Totals
--------------------------------------------------

The backend already accepts this option.

If totals are available in the response, render them.

If the backend has not implemented this yet, prepare the frontend so no redesign is needed later.

--------------------------------------------------
8. Subtotals
--------------------------------------------------

Prepare the UI so subtotal rows can be displayed later.

Do not redesign the grid when backend support is added.

--------------------------------------------------
9. Expand / Collapse
--------------------------------------------------

When there are multiple row fields:

Support expanding and collapsing groups.

Users should be able to expand one group without expanding every group.

Remember the expansion state after sorting or filtering whenever possible.

--------------------------------------------------
10. Pivot Statistics Panel
--------------------------------------------------

Above the grid, display:

Dataset Name

Sheet Name

Source Rows

Rows After Filters

Pivot Rows Returned

Layout

Date Grouping

Aggregations Used

This information already exists in the response metadata.

--------------------------------------------------
11. Search
--------------------------------------------------

Add a global search box above the grid.

Searching should filter the visible pivot rows instantly.

--------------------------------------------------
12. Export
--------------------------------------------------

Add an Export button.

For now:

Export exactly what is currently displayed in the grid to Excel.

Include:

headers

visible rows

sorting

filters

Do not export hidden columns.

This export is only for the pivot result.

Raw data export will come later.

--------------------------------------------------
13. Performance
--------------------------------------------------

Avoid re-rendering the entire grid unnecessarily.

Reuse AG Grid APIs whenever possible.

Datasets with several thousand pivot rows should remain responsive.

--------------------------------------------------
14. Empty States
--------------------------------------------------

Show friendly messages when:

No dataset selected

No pivot generated

No rows returned

Invalid response

--------------------------------------------------
